Zach Allen was excellent in Week 9, tallying four solos, one assist, one sack, one tackle for loss, and two passes defended. Chase Young showed up again in Week 9, this time recording two solos, one sack, and one tackle for loss. Josh Sweat was excellent in Week 9, tacking up two solos, two sacks, two tackles for loss, and one pass defended. Now up to seven sacks on the season, Sweat is an easy DL2 play regardless of opponent. Treat him as such for a plus Week 10 matchup against the Seattle Seahawks.

Bosa was excellent in Week 9, racking up two solos, one assist, one sack, and two tackles for loss. The older Bosa is up to four sacks on the season, with a sack in each of his last two games. Fire Bosa up as a top-25 option, thanks to a plus Week 10 matchup against the Miami Dolphins.

Chaisson showed up in Week 9, racking up two solos, one sack, two assists, and one forced fumble. The former first round pick remains inconsistent; he had dud in between this outburst and his season-best fantasy output in Week 7, but is finally emerging. Jaelan was excellent in Week 9, racking up three solos, one assist, one sack, and one tackle for loss. Leonard Williams showed up in Week 9, tallying three solos, two assists, one sack, and one tackle for loss. Oweh was excellent in Week 9, racking up two solos, one assist, two sacks, and two tackles for loss. Nelson went off in Week 8, stacking two solos, two assists, two sacks, two tackles for loss, one forced fumble, one interception, one pass defended, and one touchdown on 63 percent of the snaps. And now that he has rewarded the team's increased confidence in him, we can expect another game with at least 60 percent of the snaps against the New England Patriots in Week 10.
